466
00:28:26.180 --> 00:28:30.220
Paul writes here in a way that makes makes a clear, direct connection

467
00:28:30.220 --> 00:28:33.620
between our prayers and the global advance of the gospel.

468
00:28:34.180 --> 00:28:37.780
I remember being challenged years ago, reading the biography of James Fraser.

469
00:28:37.780 --> 00:28:41.260
He was a missionary in the kind of early 20th century.

470
00:28:41.260 --> 00:28:43.980
He was serving amongst the Lisu people in Western China.

471
00:28:44.420 --> 00:28:48.180
And they were hard people to work amongst.

472
00:28:48.460 --> 00:28:51.900
And but he really believed in the power of prayer.

473
00:28:51.900 --> 00:28:55.380
And he used to gather groups together back in England or write to them

474
00:28:55.380 --> 00:28:58.060
and encourage them to gather together to pray.

475
00:28:58.420 --> 00:29:00.060
And it wasn't just a kind of token thing.

476
00:29:00.060 --> 00:29:01.980
That's not how we viewed it. Here's what he wrote.

477
00:29:01.980 --> 00:29:03.860
He said, I am not asking you.

478
00:29:03.860 --> 00:29:06.060
This is in writing to one of those prayer groups.

479
00:29:06.060 --> 00:29:10.580
He says, I'm not writing to ask you to give help in prayer as a sort of

480
00:29:10.620 --> 00:29:14.980
sideline, but I'm trying to roll the main responsibility

481
00:29:14.980 --> 00:29:18.340
of this prayer warfare on to you.

482
00:29:18.540 --> 00:29:22.700
I want you to take the burden of these people on your shoulders.

483
00:29:22.700 --> 00:29:26.300
I want you to wrestle with God for them.

484
00:29:27.340 --> 00:29:30.140
You could then go on later to read about the the impact of the

485
00:29:30.140 --> 00:29:32.180
gospel amongst this specific people group.

486
00:29:32.180 --> 00:29:36.100
No doubt there was a direct connection with the prayers of God's people.

487
00:29:36.100 --> 00:29:40.580
Now, I don't I don't presume to know how God is going to use your prayers,

488
00:29:40.580 --> 00:29:42.700
but I do believe that God will use them.

489
00:29:43.540 --> 00:29:49.980
As part of his global purpose to advance the gospel for the glory of his name.

490
00:29:50.980 --> 00:29:53.660
So we should take an interest in our mission partners.

491
00:29:54.180 --> 00:29:57.020
We should get involved in what they're doing, especially through prayer.

492
00:29:57.500 --> 00:30:00.100
We should also imitate their example.

493
00:30:02.300 --> 00:30:03.300
What do I say that?

494
00:30:03.300 --> 00:30:06.460
Say that because it's a bit hypocritical to pray something for somebody

495
00:30:06.460 --> 00:30:08.900
else that you would be unwilling to do yourself.

496
00:30:09.460 --> 00:30:13.100
You know, as though like, yep, we want them to make Christ known somewhere else.

497
00:30:13.100 --> 00:30:15.900
But don't pray that for us here.

498
00:30:16.500 --> 00:30:19.500
They might be carrying out a different role in a different context,

499
00:30:19.500 --> 00:30:22.700
but the mission is the same wherever you are.

500
00:30:25.500 --> 00:30:27.900
Is there anything the church could learn from Paul's example here?

501
00:30:27.900 --> 00:30:32.500
Well, certainly about living as Christ's ambassadors right where we are.

502
00:30:32.900 --> 00:30:36.300
Living as people who are part of his kingdom.

503
00:30:36.500 --> 00:30:37.500
His kingdom.

504
00:30:38.900 --> 00:30:43.700
How about praying for boldness to speak of Christ to others and clarity

505
00:30:43.700 --> 00:30:45.900
in doing that here in our context?

506
00:30:46.700 --> 00:30:49.580
How about being willing to suffer for his name?

507
00:30:49.580 --> 00:30:53.580
I mean, it's almost ridiculous to even say that thinking about like Paul in prison.

508
00:30:53.900 --> 00:30:59.140
A couple of weeks ago, there were 70 believers in Congo who were beheaded

509
00:30:59.140 --> 00:31:02.660
for their faith and were found in a church.

510
00:31:02.660 --> 00:31:05.900
And we could talk about immense suffering that's going around the world today.

511
00:31:05.900 --> 00:31:08.980
The people are by the grace of God standing firm.

512
00:31:13.180 --> 00:31:18.740
So we should be willing to suffer, I don't know, mockery or the role of people's eyes

513
00:31:18.740 --> 00:31:21.180
or whatever for the sake of his name.

514
00:31:21.180 --> 00:31:23.180
He is worth it.

515
00:31:23.180 --> 00:31:28.180
And engaging well with our mission partners and being and being more familiar

516
00:31:28.180 --> 00:31:31.620
with what is happening in other places can really stir our hearts

517
00:31:31.620 --> 00:31:34.860
to be on mission right where we are here.

518
00:31:36.900 --> 00:31:40.900
But the fact that we're being asked to pray for all of these things reminds us

519
00:31:40.900 --> 00:31:43.300
of where our strength comes from.

520
00:31:43.300 --> 00:31:44.700
It comes from the Lord.

521
00:31:44.700 --> 00:31:48.700
He will enable us to be faithful as partners in the gospel.

522
00:31:49.300 --> 00:31:52.900
So this brings us to the final words of benediction in the letter.

523
00:31:52.900 --> 00:31:57.500
Paul speaks here, reminding us once again that our God is a God of peace

524
00:31:57.500 --> 00:32:03.300
and love and grace and that has been shown to us in Jesus.

525
00:32:05.900 --> 00:32:07.220
So we can know peace with God.

526
00:32:07.220 --> 00:32:10.340
We can know his love and his grace, not because of the amount of hours

527
00:32:10.340 --> 00:32:15.340
we've logged in prayer or how faithful we've been in proclaiming the gospel,

528
00:32:15.340 --> 00:32:18.980
you know, how many people we've shared it with or whatever.

529
00:32:18.980 --> 00:32:24.420
We can know all of those things through Jesus by the help of the Spirit.

530
00:32:25.100 --> 00:32:28.500
And it's interesting as we close out this letter, he speaks about.

531
00:32:30.500 --> 00:32:34.260
This is his grace be with all of you who love our Lord Jesus Christ

532
00:32:34.260 --> 00:32:35.860
with love incorruptible.

533
00:32:35.860 --> 00:32:38.100
He's already spoken about grace and peace and love.

534
00:32:38.620 --> 00:32:42.700
But this is the first time he speaks about our love for God.

535
00:32:43.460 --> 00:32:46.420
So everything that we've learned together in Ephesians isn't just there

536
00:32:46.420 --> 00:32:49.700
so we might we might learn things about God or about the church

537
00:32:49.700 --> 00:32:51.460
or or do things for him.

538
00:32:52.060 --> 00:32:55.620
It's most fundamentally that we might know God himself

539
00:32:56.020 --> 00:33:00.020
and that we might love God with all of our hearts.

540
00:33:00.820 --> 00:33:05.540
So as we know him, his grace, his peace and his love, the right response

541
00:33:05.540 --> 00:33:11.180
is to is to love him to receive his love for us and to enter into this

542
00:33:11.180 --> 00:33:14.660
loving relationship that will last forever.

543
00:33:14.980 --> 00:33:16.380
Let's pray together, shall we?

544
00:33:19.780 --> 00:33:22.900
Well, we look forward to the day when the battles that we face

545
00:33:22.900 --> 00:33:28.340
in this life will be over and we will be with you forever more.

546
00:33:29.300 --> 00:33:35.540
But I pray that even now on this day that we would stand firm, rest assured

547
00:33:35.540 --> 00:33:41.020
that we are loved by you in Christ and that you have provided all that

548
00:33:41.020 --> 00:33:44.020
we need that we might stand for him.

549
00:33:44.900 --> 00:33:48.060
It's Lord, I pray that by the help of your spirit that we would come

550
00:33:48.060 --> 00:33:52.740
to you, that we would come to know you as the God who has welcomed us in him.

551
00:33:53.780 --> 00:33:57.060
And Lord, I pray that you would help us to be people as we just thought

552
00:33:57.060 --> 00:34:03.140
about, we would be people of prayer and who have a living relationship with you

553
00:34:03.660 --> 00:34:06.740
and people who are faithful in partnering together for the sake of the

554
00:34:06.740 --> 00:34:09.220
gospel, both locally and globally.

555
00:34:10.100 --> 00:34:11.540
We ask all this in Jesus' name.

556
00:34:11.940 --> 00:34:12.340
Amen.

